Senior Performance & Reliability Engineer (Rotating)
01 May 2014 04:44 PM - UAE
..Scope of Duties : a) Review plant information concerning assigned analysis activities to determine what actual problem requires resolution and obtain any additional information needed to understand the problem. (b) Establishes and maintains file for each analysis to assure future feedback can be analyzed for proactive improvements. (c) Diagnoses problems to determine the root cause. Identifies and obtains assistance as necessary in order to determine the root cause, whether from other departments within company or from outside contractors as required. (d) Supervises the work of contractors during the execution of any assistance needed for problem resolution (including contract and material issues) or for any special studies. (e) Ensures that the work is integrated with that of other Departments and Divisions to prevent duplication of efforts. P&R; analysis will be poader scope than typical work performed by other Divisions and Departments. (f) Works with other Divisions and Departments to ensure the provision of adequate service. This includes obtaining service agreements where necessary and providing time estimates for work completion and advising the Divisions/Departments of relevant priorities. (g) Carries out technical review at all stages of Plant modifications and subsequent construction and implementation to verify modifications satisfy the expectations of the P&RD; recommended action. (h) Keeps apeast of changes in relevant standards and improvements in associated technology, equipment design, and maintenance practices to support proactive resolution of problems under review by P&RD.; (i) Provides information to the Head, Performance & Reliability as necessary for the preparation and planning of schedules and for issues requiring reporting to higher levels of management. (j) Provides rotating engineering expertise assistance to other P&RD; engineers during the development of resolutions by them. (k) Directs and supervises on-the-job training and instruction of assigned trainees. (l) Ensures that reports are prepared for problem resolution that are complete, including basic recommended action plan, general costs, timing for action, reasons why action is necessary, and what are risks if action is not taken by responsible group. (m) Track implementation of recommended actions to assure that action taken satisfies the expectations for problem resolution. (n) Reviews completed problem solutions with other activities to identify lessons learned that could be utilized in other applications. Minimum Requirements : â¢ B. Sc. In Mechanical Engineering or equivalent. â¢ 12 years engineering experience in the oil refining or petrochemical industry, including at least 6 years supervisory experience. â¢ Good knowledge of spoken and written English. â¢ Computer literate. Note: please note that only Romanian candidates can apply for this post since it's International Romanian Campaign. Applicant Require (more...)
